      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "## Oxalic Acid (Ethanedioic Acid) — pKa Values\n\nOxalic acid (H₂C₂O₄) is a **diprotic acid** with **2 dissociation steps**:\n\n1. **H₂L ⇌ HL⁻ + H⁺** (first dissociation)\n2. **HL⁻ ⇌ L²⁻ + H⁺** (second dissociation)\n\nThe SRD-46 database records the following representative pKa brackets for oxalic acid (ligand_8872):\n\n| Dissociation Step | Equilibrium | pKa (representative) |\n|---|---|---|\n| pKa₁ | H₂L ⇌ HL⁻ + H⁺ | **~1.2** |\n| pKa₂ | HL⁻ ⇌ L²⁻ + H⁺ | **~3.8** |\n\nThese values correspond to the two protonation equilibria cataloged as:\n- **beta_def_32**: [HL] + [H] ⇌ [H₂L] (18 measurements in SRD-46)\n- **beta_def_79**: [L] + [H] ⇌ [HL] (38 measurements in SRD-46)",
